  "texts": [
    "The initial formation of human habits is also a kind of unsupervised training.",
    "\"Habit is an ability,…formed through past experience\" (Dewey, 2008b, p. 48).",
    "Before adjustment and reconstruction, habits emerge in an unsupervised manner.",
    "Therefore, in the first stage of Dewey's moral growth theory, habit and instinct are juxtaposed (Dewey, 2008a).",
    "After pre-training on extensive data, LLMs exhibit characteristics of emergence and homogenization."
